outstanding class of individuals from India and abroad. The entire process is rigorous and holistic, and involves context specific review. We acknowledge that there are varying levels of access and privilege for different candidates, and as such, each applicant’s submission is reviewed in the applicant’s context.  Application Written Test Interview     Ashoka University’s need-based Financial Aid programme aims to provide necessary financial support which can help you bridge the gap between the cost of the programme and your ability to pay. Several benefactors, including YIF alumni, have made financial aid possible.  of Fellows 2020-21 are on some form of need-based financial aid  of Fellows 2020-21 are on more than 50% tuition waivers  of all Fellows to date have been supported through financial aid         The Young India Fellowship has a growing and vibrant community of international students. Countries represented in our international community include United Kingdom, United States of America, Ireland, France, Pakistan, Ukraine, and more. If you are an international student, the YIF is a worthwhile opportunity for you to experience a multidisciplinary education that has a global outlook, while being rooted in Indian ethos. Please contact the office of admissions, we look forward to speaking with you.                        Programme Interested InUndergraduate ProgrammeYoung India FellowshipYSPPhDMA - EconomicsMA EnglishMSC Biology Year of Admission2022-232023-242024-252025-26  Subscribe to our communications [current_url]     Plot No. 2, Rajiv Gandhi Education City, National Capital Region P.O. Rai, Sonepat         Haryana-131029 (India)  Ashoka University Plot no.222, Second floor, Okhla Industrial Estate, Phase III, New Delhi-110020        Email Address*                  Copyright © Ashoka University: Leading Liberal Arts and Sciences University              ",ab576a3f-a969-4a1c-91c3-a0402954390d
